article.headline: St. Bonaventure 97, Duquesne 94
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- A.J. Hawkins scored 29 points and reserve Tyler Benson added 24 points as St. Bonaventure weathered a second-half Duquesne comeback to end a six-game losing streak, beating the Dukes 97-94 Saturday night. Benson was averaging 2.2 points and had never previously scored more than nine points in a game for the Bonnies (7-20, 4-10 in Atlantic 10). Duquesne (10-16, 6-9) trailed by as many as 22 points and was down 52-33 at halftime, but rallied to within three points several times as Robert Mitchell scored 15 of his 18 points in the second half before fouling out. The Dukes had several chances to tie it, but Hawkins hit a jumper with 1:34 remaining to make it 91-86. Kieron Achara had 26 points for the Dukes, who lost their fifth in a row after winning five consecutive games. The Dukes are 5-6 since junking their previous system and going with a pressing, trapping defense and hurry-up offense. Despite losing, Duquesne clinched a spot in the Atlantic 10 tournament when La Salle lost to George Washington 86-74. St. Bonaventure currently holds the 12th and final spot in the tournament. Duquesne forced 29 turnovers by team it beat 111-92 on the road Feb. 3, but St. Bonaventure shot 52 percent (30-of-58) to the Dukes' 37 percent (28-of-75). Hawkins had 12 rebounds and Michael Lee had 14 St. Bonaventure held a 52-30 rebounding edge.
